 mso-width-relative:page;mso-height-relative:page'>
 <v:imagedata src=3D"Screen_EmpireSummary_files/image004.png" o:title=3D""/>
 <w:wrap type=3D"square" anchorx=3D"page"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=3D467 height=3D350
src=3D"Screen_EmpireSummary_files/image003.png" align=3Dright hspace=3D12 v=
:shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_0"><![endif]><span
style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>When playing as a pirate your sources of income =
are
different. Most income is more variable, so it can be harder to plan cashfl=
ow.
Your expenses can also be highly variable.</span></p>

<h3><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Bonuses<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>At the bottom-left the Bonuses panel summarizes any bo=
nuses
from the alien races within your empire. Also listed here are any bonuses f=
rom
special ruins at your colonies.</p>

<h3><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Ships and Bases<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>The Ships and Bases p=
anel at
the bottom-right provides a summary of all the ships and bases in your empi=
re,
including firepower and maintenance costs.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h3><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Changing your Government<o:p></o:p></s=
pan></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>In the government sec=
tion is
a dropdown list allowing you to choose a new type of government for your
empire. Click the &#8220;Have Revolution&#8221; button to change your
government. Note that a revolution is never painless; there will probably be
unwanted side effects...<o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

